    <title>Authentication Endpoints</title>
    <para condition="client">Use the following global endpoint to access the Rackspace Cloud v 2.0 Identity service:</para>
    <para condition="client"><guilabel>Endpoint.</guilabel>
        <link xlink:href="https://identity.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0">https://identity.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0</link>
        </para>
    <para condition="admin">Use the following global endpoints to access the Rackspace Cloud v 2.0 Identity service:</para>
        <itemizedlist condition="admin">
            <listitem>
                <para><guilabel>Production endpoint.</guilabel>
                    <link xlink:href="https://identity.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0">
                        https://identity.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0</link>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><guilabel>Staging endpoint.</guilabel>
                    <link xlink:href="https://staging.identity-internal.api.rackspacecloud.com/">
                        https://identity.api.rackspacecloud.com/v2.0</link>
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    <warning>
        <para>To avoid connection issues caused by DNS changes, always use the full Identity
            service endpoint when making API requests. Do not use the IP address.</para>
    </warning>
